thy Father gaue thée, will be no constraint, if his counsayle
will not commaunde thée, if his warning wil not
make thée warie, nor his aduice be thy aduertisement:
yet let imminent perills, and insuing daungers bée a
precious preseruatiue against future calamities. Consider
with thy selfe Gwydonius, what difference is betwéene
fréedome and bondage, betwéene libertie and
captiuitie, mirth and mourning, pleasure and payne,
rest and care, happinesse and heauinesse: and so farre
dooth he which is frée frō affection differ from him which
is fettered in fancie.
            Why but Gwydonius, why doost thou thus recklesly
rage against reason? Why doost thou thus fondly exclayme
agaynst thine owne welfare? Why doost thou
condempne thy selfe of that crime whereof thou art not
guyltie.
